Investment group Reinet increased its net asset value (NAV) by €289m to €5.5bn in the six months to end-September, the group announced on Tuesday. Dividends received from British American Tobacco, which forms 67.3% of Reinet’s NAV, amounted to €127m. The management fee for the period was unchanged at €23m, compared with the year-earlier period. Growth in NAV reflected a compound return of 16% a year in euro terms since March 2009, including dividends paid, the group said. Reinet shares were up 0.38% to R26.65 in early morning trade on the JSE.